= RESEARCH & RESEARCH METHODOLOGY

== Research

Research is a systematic and scientific process of collecting, analyzing, and
interpreting data to solve a problem or answer a question.

OR

Research is a careful and organized investigation undertaken to discover new
knowledge or verify existing facts. Key Characteristics

CHARACTERISTICS:

/ Systematic: follows a proper plan or method.
/ Objective: free from bias.
/ Logical: based on reasoning.
/ Empirical: based on observation or data.
/ Replicable: can be repeated by others.

== Research Methodology

Research Methodology is the systematic way of solving a research problem using
scientific methods and techniques.

OR

Research Methodology refers to the methods, procedures, and techniques used by a
researcher to conduct research.

It explains how research is done and why a particular method is used.

CHARACTERISTICS:

/ Systematic: Follows a step-by-step organized procedure.
/ Logical: Based on reasoning and clear thinking.
/ Objective: Free from personal bias or opinions.
/ Empirical: Based on real data, observation, or experiments.
/ Scientific: Uses scientific methods and principles.
/ Replicable: Other researchers can repeat the study.
/ Controlled: Variables are properly managed and controlled.
/ Analytical: Involves proper data analysis and interpretation.

== Characteristics of Technical Methodology

/ Problem-Oriented: Focuses on solving practical or real-world technical problems.
/ Scientific Approach: Uses scientific principles, formulas, and experiments.
/ Systematic Process: Follows step-by-step procedures (design, testing, analysis).
/ Application-Based: Results are used in engineering, IT, industry, etc.
/ Innovative: Aims to develop new technologies, tools, or improvements.
/ Data-Driven: Based on measurable data and technical analysis.
/ Experimental: Often involves laboratory testing, simulations, or prototypes.
/ Objective: Accurate: Requires precision and accuracy in results.

